title: PML-N’s Khawaja Waseem wins PP-57 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League Nawaz (PML-N) candidate, Khawaja Muhammad Waseem has won the election for Punjab Assembly constituency PP-57, Narowal-IV by securing 52,272 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Independent candidate, Rana Lal Badshah who bagged 26,480 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 49.91%.
